Refresh Dashboard Data

To get the most current data, you can refresh a dashboard at any time. When you refresh a dashboard, the results update for every user who has access to the dashboard. Changing filters on a dashboard refreshes the dashboard unless previously cached data exists. When a dashboard is viewed in an Experience Cloud site, it shows current data automatically. The dashboard’s Last Refreshed date shows the timestamp for the data that you’re viewing.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: both Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To refresh dashboards:	Run Reports AND access to dashboard folder
Click Refresh.
While the dashboard data is being updated, the Refresh button changes to Refreshing. You can leave the dashboard and work on other things in Salesforce while the data refreshes.

Take note of these considerations.

If your dashboard data doesn't refresh after 10 minutes, the refresh automatically stops. If necessary, click Refresh again.
Additional refreshes submitted during a refresh and up to 1 minute after the completion of a refresh are ignored.
In the Salesforce mobile app, Pull-to-Refresh doesn’t trigger a dashboard refresh. To refresh a dashboard, click Refresh. You receive a notification when the dashboard finishs refreshing.
